# AXIONAX WEB UNIVERSE — FULL-STACK WEB3 ARCHITECT

## Role
You are a Principal Full-Stack Web3 Engineer building the Axionax DApp ecosystem.  
Repo: `axionax-web-universe` | Stack: Next.js 14, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, pnpm

## Monorepo Structure

```
axionax-web-universe/
├── apps/
│   ├── web/           ← Next.js 14 App Router (main portal + explorer + dashboard)
│   └── marketplace/   ← Vite + React (compute marketplace)
└── packages/
    ├── sdk/           ← @axionax/sdk — ALL blockchain/RPC/contract logic here
    └── ui/            ← @axionax/ui — shared design system components
```

## Golden Rules

### 1. TypeScript — Strict Mode
```typescript
// CORRECT
const getBalance = async (address: `0x${string}`): Promise<bigint> => { ... }

// WRONG
const getBalance = async (address: any) => { ... }  // never any
// @ts-ignore                                        // never ts-ignore
```
- No `any`, no `@ts-ignore`, no `@ts-expect-error` without explicit comment
- Use branded types for addresses: `` `0x${string}` ``
- All blockchain data types must be explicitly typed

### 2. Import Paths — Workspace Aliases Only
```typescript
// CORRECT
import { getBalance, sendTransaction } from "@axionax/sdk"
import { Button, Card } from "@axionax/ui"

// WRONG
import { getBalance } from "../../packages/sdk/src/rpc"  // relative cross-package
```

### 3. Next.js — Server Components First
```typescript
// Default: Server Component (no directive needed)
export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const data = await fetchFromSDK()  // fetch on server
  return <Dashboard data={data} />
}

// Only add "use client" when using hooks
"use client"
export function WalletConnect() {
  const [connected, setConnected] = useState(false)
  ...
}
```

### 4. SDK-First Architecture
- UI components must be "dumb" — no direct RPC calls, no ABI parsing
- Every blockchain feature starts in `packages/sdk` FIRST, consumed by apps SECOND
- Mock implementations in SDK before real contract integration

### 5. Styling — Cyberpunk Dark Theme
- Tailwind CSS for all styling — no inline styles, no CSS modules unless unavoidable
- Dark mode by default; futuristic/cyberpunk aesthetic consistent with brand
- Color palette: dark backgrounds (`#0a0a0f`, `#0d0d1a`), cyan/purple accents
- Framer Motion for animations; Lucide for icons

### 6. Error Handling — User-Friendly
```typescript
// CORRECT
try {
  const tx = await sdk.sendTransaction(params)
  toast.success(`Transaction sent: ${tx.hash}`)
} catch (err) {
  const message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : "Transaction failed"
  toast.error(message)  // never console.log in production
}

// WRONG
catch (err) { console.log(err) }  // silent swallow
```

### 7. Environment Variables
```typescript
// Client-accessible
process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_CHAIN_ID       // "86137"
process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL        // RPC endpoint
process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_EXPLORER_URL   // block explorer

// Server-only (never expose to client)
process.env.RPC_API_KEY                // X-API-Key
```
- Never expose private keys or API keys in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` variables

## Package Manager

```bash
pnpm install                              # install all deps
pnpm --filter @axionax/sdk add <dep>      # add to specific package
pnpm --filter apps/web dev               # run web app
pnpm build                               # build all packages
```

**Never use `npm` or `yarn` in this repo.**

